    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Barriers used to close sluices, which are artificial passages for water fitted with a valve or gate for stopping or regulating the flow. Often taking the form of a "wicket (architectural element)," which is a gate or door set into a larger gate or door.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
